items.name: Streamlit
items.description: This repository contains various exercises I have worked on to deepen my understanding of the Streamlit framework. Streamlit is an open-source app framework specifically for Machine Learning and Data Science projects. It allows you to create beautiful, interactive web applications directly from your Python code.

items.name: TE-PF-Prediction
items.description: This repository is used to store data and code related to the paper "A Machine Learning-Based Framework for Predicting the Power Factor of Thermoelectric Materials."

items.name: Recommendation-system-
items.description: A Streamlit-Based Recommendation System is a web application that provides personalized recommendations to users using machine learning algorithms. Streamlit, a Python-based framework, allows for rapid prototyping and deployment of interactive applications with minimal coding effort.

items.name: SSH-Shell-Attacks
items.description: Project for Machine Learning for Networking Exam @ Polito - SSH Shell Attacks Analysis: a project to classify attacker tactics and identify patterns in 230,000 honeypot-captured Unix shell attacks using MITRE ATT&CK framework and ML techniques.

items.name: SSH-Shell-Attacks
items.description: Project for Machine Learning for Networking Exam @ Polito - SSH Shell Attacks Analysis: a project to classify attacker tactics and identify patterns in 230,000 honeypot-captured Unix shell attacks using MITRE ATT&CK framework and ML techniques.

items.name: Option-pricing-model
items.description: An Option Pricing Model based on the framework of Black-Scholes and Monte Carlo model using python. This model compares the solutions obtained by both the models and includes risk analysis and volatility prediction of europian call option using machine learning

items.name: paxml
items.description: Pax is a Jax-based machine learning framework for training large scale models. Pax allows for advanced and fully configurable experimentation and parallelization, and has demonstrated industry leading model flop utilization rates.
